GJPD: Woman suspected of DUI in Orchard Mesa with dog in car arrested
Photo: David Jones
By Jay Greene&nbsp|&nbsp
Posted: Tue 5:31 AM, May 03, 2016
ORCHARD MESA, Colo.-- A woman suspected of driving under the influence with a dog in the car in Orchard Mesa Monday night was arrested, according to the Grand Junction Police Department.
Around 9:45 p.m. police responded to a single-car crash on Highway 50, near Palmer Street, in front of the El Rio Rancho Motel, where a woman drove onto the median in a construction zone.
Authorities said she failed a sobriety test. She was taken to jail on suspicion of driving under the influence.
She nor the dog were hurt.
Police held on to the poodle, but no word on if it will be returned to the owner.
